<item>
            <title>[SPR-495] CookieLocaleResolver save cookie false with Tomcat 5.5.4</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-495</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using CookieLocaleResolver with a Application running on Tomcat 5.5.4 the saved cookie is false. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The right format should be: &lt;br/&gt;
de_DE or en_US  &lt;br/&gt;
but in Tomcat 5.5.4 the cookie will be saved like this: &lt;br/&gt;
&quot;de_DE_&quot; or &quot;en_US_&quot;    &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the quotation mark and the last blank are false.    &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have this Problem with my own application and with the countries sample only on Tomcat 5.5.4 (other 5.5 versions was not tested).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mfg Matthias&lt;/p&gt;</description>
