                            <comment id="11705" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 7 Dec 2004 05:10:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report! This indeed only comes into effect on Tomcat 5.5... On the other hand, I detected wrong parsing on Resin too: There, only the language code gets parsed from a given cookie, never the country code or variant.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I solved both by changing CookieLocaleResolver&apos;s cookie value separator from space to underscore. Spaces in cookie values do not seem to be properly supported across servlet containers; both Tomcat 5.5 and Resin mess up when parsing such cookie values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For backwards compatibility reasons, CookieLocaleResolver will also accept cookie values with space as separator. However, it will always create cookie values with underscores now, following java.util.Locale&apos;s &quot;toString&quot; format (&quot;en&quot;, &quot;en_UK&quot;, etc).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
